          <h2>CUET 2026 Exam Overview:</h2>
          <p>The Common University Entrance Test (CUET) 2026 is the mandatory national-level entrance exam for admission into undergraduate programs at all Central Universities in India, along with numerous State, Private, and Deemed universities. Conducted by the National Testing Agency (NTA), it provides a single-window opportunity for Class 12 students to secure seats in top-tier institutions like DU, BHU, and JNU.</p>
          <p><strong>Key Highlights for CUET 2026</strong></p>
          <p><strong>Exam Date (Tentative):</strong> May 11 – May 31, 2026 (Conducted in multiple shifts).<br>
          <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Must have passed or be appearing in the Class 12/equivalent examination.<br>
          <strong>Exam Mode:</strong> Computer-Based Test (CBT).</p>
          <p><strong>Exam Pattern &amp; Syllabus</strong></p>
          <p>The exam is structured into three sections:</p>
          <p><strong>1. Section I (Languages):</strong> Tests proficiency through Reading Comprehension, Vocabulary, and Literary Aptitude. Includes 13 main Indian languages and 20 optional foreign/regional languages.<br>
          <strong>2. Section II (Domain Subjects):</strong> Covers 23 specific subjects (e.g., Physics, Accountancy, History). Syllabus is strictly mapped to NCERT Class 12.<br>
          <strong>3. Section III (General Test):</strong> Covers General Knowledge, Current Affairs, Numerical Ability, and Logical &amp; Analytical Reasoning.</p>
          <p><strong>Questions are MCQs. Correct answers award +5 marks, while incorrect MCQs carry a -1 penalty.</strong></p>
